Gauteng is expected to have cold conditions from Thursday, spokesperson for South African Weather Service Vanetia Phakola said today.The service said the Johannesburg and Pretoria would mostly be fine and cool, with temperatures dropping on Friday and picking up again on Sunday.Phakola said Vereeniging residents would be the first to feel the biting cold. The storm is mostly affecting the Western Cape but in Gauteng we will start feeling the cold weather in Vereeniging on Thursday afternoon, and Pretoria and Johannesburg will start feeling the cold on Thursday evening, Phakola added.The agency has warned of strong gale winds, which would continue in the Western Cape this morning with the speed of between 60km/h and 90km/h.The winds will move to the Northern Cape and western areas of the Eastern Cape later on Thursday.-TNA Reporter